From: Edwin Peer <edwin.peer@broadcom.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Sep 2021 05:32:34 -0700
Subject: RDMA/bnxt_re: Use separate response buffer for stat_ctx_free
Patch-mainline: v5.16-rc1
Git-commit: 403bc4359a0098712b917bc4ae18349d5ae11ca3
References: jsc#SLE-18977

Use separate buffers for the request and response data. Eventhough the
response data is not used, providing the correct length is appropriate.

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/1631709163-2287-4-git-send-email-selvin.xavier@broadcom.com
Signed-off-by: Edwin Peer <edwin.peer@broadcom.com>
Reviewed-by: Leon Romanovsky <leonro@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Selvin Xavier <selvin.xavier@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: Jason Gunthorpe <jgg@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/main.c |    7 ++++---
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/main.c
+++ b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/main.c
@@ -525,7 +525,8 @@ static int bnxt_re_net_stats_ctx_free(st
 				      u32 fw_stats_ctx_id)
 {
 	struct bnxt_en_dev *en_dev = rdev->en_dev;
-	struct hwrm_stat_ctx_free_input req = {0};
+	struct hwrm_stat_ctx_free_input req = {};
+	struct hwrm_stat_ctx_free_output resp = {};
 	struct bnxt_fw_msg fw_msg;
 	int rc = -EINVAL;
 
@@ -539,8 +540,8 @@ static int bnxt_re_net_stats_ctx_free(st
 
 	bnxt_re_init_hwrm_hdr(rdev, (void *)&req, HWRM_STAT_CTX_FREE, -1, -1);
 	req.stat_ctx_id = cpu_to_le32(fw_stats_ctx_id);
-	bnxt_re_fill_fw_msg(&fw_msg, (void *)&req, sizeof(req), (void *)&req,
-			    sizeof(req), DFLT_HWRM_CMD_TIMEOUT);
+	bnxt_re_fill_fw_msg(&fw_msg, (void *)&req, sizeof(req), (void *)&resp,
+			    sizeof(resp), DFLT_HWRM_CMD_TIMEOUT);
 	rc = en_dev->en_ops->bnxt_send_fw_msg(en_dev, BNXT_ROCE_ULP, &fw_msg);
 	if (rc)
 		ibdev_err(&rdev->ibdev, "Failed to free HW stats context %#x",
